<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,249]" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis box="[199,325,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
Dedicated to the late professor Janusz Wojtusiak (1942–2012), who was a great entomologist and our educator, mentor, Academic teacher, and showed us how to love tropical butterflies. The species name “ianusca” is freely formed by Latinising the word “Janusz” and treating it as a female noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
